cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper is about training deep neural networks that are verifiably robust to adversarial perturbations. The paper discusses the use of interval bound propagation (IBP) to achieve this goal. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the security aspect of the trained models, which makes cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new method for training verifiably robust models, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
